```

This is based on #1474, but it changes the input parser file and uses the parser generator.

Adding support for multiple GameWindow(s) within a single game.

This is only implemented for WINDOWS && DIRECTX

Non-primary windows do not handle any input and for input events to reach the users game the primary window must be active. This can be improved at a later time when it is a needed feature.

The existing Game / Platform / GraphicsDevice code is largely unchanged and only deals directly with the standard, primary window which it also creates.

Example:

```
// In Game.Initialize()
window = GameWindow.CreateWindow(this, 640, 480);
window.Title = "Second Game Window";
swapChain = new SwapChainRenderTarget(GraphicsDevice, window.Handle, 640, 480);

// In Game.Draw()
GraphicsDevice.SetRenderTarget(swapChain);
GraphicsDevice.Clear(Color.Red);
GraphicsDevice.Present();
GraphicsDevice.SetRenderTarget(null);
```

Adding support for multiple GameWindow(s) within a single game.

This is only implemented for WINDOWS && DIRECTX

Non-primary windows do not handle any input and for input events to reach the users game the primary window must be active. This can be improved at a later time when it is a needed feature.

The existing Game / Platform / GraphicsDevice code is largely unchanged and only deals directly with the standard, primary window which it also creates.

Any additional windows will be created by the users game code, example:

```
MyGame::Initialize()
{
    base.Initialize();

    // Create an additional window.
    GameWindow.Create(Game, Width, Height);

    // Create a SwapChain to render the window
    SwapChain = new SwapChainRenderTarget(windowHandle: Window.Handle,
                                            graphicsDevice: _device,
                                            width: Window.ClientBounds.Width,
                                            height: Window.ClientBounds.Height,
                                            mipMap: false,
                                            presentInterval: PresentInterval.Default,
                                            surfaceFormat: SurfaceFormat.Color,
                                            depthFormat: DepthFormat.Depth16,
                                            preferredMultiSampleCount: 1,
                                            usage: RenderTargetUsage.DiscardContents);
}
```

Secondary windows must be rendered before the primary, and is done by embedding code like this within your draw method:

```
MyGame::Draw(GameTime)
{
        _device.SetRenderTarget(SwapChain);

        // Draw stuff...

        SwapChain.Present();

        // Setup to draw to primary window like this...
        _device.SetRenderTarget(null);

        // Draw to primary window
        // Done.
        base.Draw(gameTime);
}
```
